g.text: AMF - Access and Mobility Management Function
* RRC (Radio Resource Control): Setting up and maintaining UE connections, handovers, and security.
* NAS signaling relay: Forwarding and managing Non-Access Stratum messages between UE and the 5G Core (AMF).
* Mobility management: Handling mobility between cells and CUs.
* Security and encryption control: Key management and ciphering control commands.
* Connection management: Establishing and releasing signaling bearers and sessions.
* PDCP layer (User Plane part): Packet routing, header compression, ciphering/deciphering.
* QoS enforcement: Per-flow QoS, scheduling coordination with DU.
* User data forwarding: Between the 5G Core (UPF) and DU(s).
In 5G's service-based architecture (SB), network functions (NFs) communicate over APIs
which act as a "common bus" to exchange messages. Each NF communicates with
the network repository function (NRF) over a RESTful API and HTTP/2 to register their
services and discover and communicate with other NFs.
